1382	\subsection*{The triple-overlap glue field \(t'\)}
1383	
1384	The scheme-gluing machine requires, beyond the pairwise transitions \(t_{I,J}\), a
1385	\emph{triple-overlap} field \(t'\) on the relevant fibre products, together with
1386	its compatibility \(t_{\mathrm{fac}}\) with the chart projections. We record both
1387	as the next layer of bridge results; their cocycle coherence is the residual
1388	obligation discharged in \cref{def:gr_glued_scheme}.
1389	
1390	\begin{definition}
1391	
1392	\leanok
1393	[The triple-overlap transition \(t'\)]
1394	  \label{def:gr_chart_transition'}
1395	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Grassmannian.chartTransition'}
1396	  \uses{def:gr_away_pullback_iso, def:gr_cocycle_theta_ij, def:gr_away_mul_comm_equiv}
1397	  The \(t'\)-field of the Grassmannian glue datum is the morphism of schemes
1398	  \[
1399	    t'_{I,J,K} : U^I_J \times_{U^I} U^I_K \longrightarrow U^J_K \times_{U^J} U^J_I ,
1400	  \]
1401	  defined as the composite
1402	  \[
1403	    U^I_J \times_{U^I} U^I_K
1404	      \xrightarrow{\ \sim\ } \Spec S_I
1405	      \xrightarrow{\ \Spec \Theta_{I,J}\ } \Spec S_J
1406	      \xrightarrow{\ \Spec \mathrm{swap}\ } \Spec R^J[1/(P^J_K P^J_I)]
1407	      \xrightarrow{\ \sim\ } U^J_K \times_{U^J} U^J_I ,
1408	  \]
1409	  where the first and last arrows are the pullback identifications of
1410	  \cref{def:gr_away_pullback_iso} -- the source one for the pair \((P^I_J, P^I_K)\)
1411	  over \(R^I\), and the target one (taken inverse) for the pair \((P^J_K, P^J_I)\)
1412	  over \(R^J\) -- the middle arrow is the \(\Spec\) of the localised
1413	  triple-overlap transition \(\Theta_{I,J} : S_J \to S_I\)
1414	  (\cref{def:gr_cocycle_theta_ij}), and \(\mathrm{swap}\) is the \(\Spec\) of the
1415	  order-swap isomorphism \(R^J[1/(P^J_K P^J_I)] \cong S_J = R^J[1/(P^J_I P^J_K)]\)
1416	  (\cref{def:gr_away_mul_comm_equiv}). The order-swap is inserted precisely to
1417	  reconcile the product order \(P^J_K P^J_I\) carried by the target pullback
1418	  identification with the order \(P^J_I P^J_K\) of the codomain \(S_J\) of
1419	  \(\Theta_{I,J}\).
1420	\end{definition}
1421	
1422	\begin{lemma}
1423	
1424	\leanok
1425	[The \(t'\) ring identity]
1426	  \label{lem:gr_chartTransition'_ringIdentity}
1427	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Grassmannian.chartTransition'_ringIdentity}
1428	  \uses{def:gr_cocycle_theta_ij, def:gr_away_mul_comm_equiv, def:gr_away_incl_right, def:gr_away_incl_left, def:gr_transition, lem:gr_awayInclRight_comp_algebraMap, lem:gr_awayMulCommEquiv_comp_algebraMap, lem:mathlib_away_lift}
1429	  Over the triple-overlap rings, the localised transition \(\Theta_{I,J}\)
1430	  (\cref{def:gr_cocycle_theta_ij}) pre-composed with the order-swap and the right
1431	  inclusion equals the left inclusion post-composed with the plain transition
1432	  \(\theta_{I,J}\), as ring homomorphisms \(R^J[1/P^J_I] \to S_I\):
1433	  \[
1434	    \Theta_{I,J} \circ \mathrm{swap} \circ \iota^{\mathrm{R}}_{P^J_K, P^J_I}
1435	      \;=\; \iota^{\mathrm{L}}_{P^I_J, P^I_K} \circ \theta_{I,J} .
1436	  \]
1437	\end{lemma}
1438	\begin{proof}
1439	  \uses{def:gr_cocycle_theta_ij, def:gr_away_mul_comm_equiv, def:gr_away_incl_right, def:gr_away_incl_left, def:gr_transition, lem:gr_awayInclRight_comp_algebraMap, lem:gr_awayMulCommEquiv_comp_algebraMap, lem:mathlib_away_lift}
1440	  \leanok
1441	  Both sides are ring maps out of the away-localisation \(R^J[1/P^J_I]\), so by the
1442	  universal property of the localisation (\cref{lem:mathlib_away_lift}) it suffices
