1752	% $U^I\times U^J$ can be seen to be the closed subscheme
1753	% $\Delta_{I,J}\subset U^I\times U^J$ defined by entries of the matrix formula
1754	% $X^J_I\,X^I - X^J =0$, and so $\grass(r,d)$ is a separated scheme."
